  The One Framework for Any Technical Question

  

  When an interviewer asks "how does X work?" use this structure:



  1. What problem does it solve? (1 sentence)

  2. How it works (2–3 sentences, no jargon)

  3. Why you chose it over alternatives (1 sentence)

  4. What result you got (1 sentence with a number)



  Example for XGBoost:



  ▎ "XGBoost solves the problem of learning from structured tabular data. It builds trees sequentially where each tree corrects the errors of the previous one — kind of like a team where each person focuses on what the last person got wrong. I chose it 

  ▎ over Random Forest because it has better regularization for smaller datasets, and over neural networks because our data is tabular not image or text. We achieved 73.47% ROC-AUC with proper cross-validation."

